cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a federated learning architecture for on-device machine learning. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper leverages blockchain technology for secure and decentralized machine learning. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper proposes a distributed learning approach where local updates are exchanged and verified using blockchain. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the consensus mechanism used in blockchain for verifying local updates. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper analyzes the end-to-end latency model of the proposed architecture, which involves communication delays.
